REQ-0-DDLN-SWH-012 Requirements Linking
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given a requirement id, one should be able to easily navigate to the requirement
 definition without any extra information.
 That is, the requirement id should uniquely identify the file where the
 requirement is defined.
 As a consequence, Reqtraq will be able to construct a link to any requirement
 referenced in a document.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Rationale: easy navigation of the requirement hierarchy is essential both
 for development and for verification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Parents: REQ-0-DDLN-SYS-001
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verification: Demonstration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Safety impact: None.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
/req
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
req:
\end_layout

\end_inset

REQ-0-DDLN-SWH-002 Uniform requirement ID format
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The RMT SHALL enforce a uniform requirement id format.
 Defined to be:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
REQ-[project/system number]-[project/system abbreviation]-[SYS or SWH or
 SWL or HWH or HWL]-[a unique alphanumeric sequence],
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
e.g.: REQ-0-DDLN-SWH-002
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is no special notation for derived requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Rationale: Tracing is only possible if Requirements have unambiguous identifiers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verification: Unit test.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Parent: REQ-0-DDLN-SYS-001
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
/req
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
req:
\end_layout

\end_inset

REQ-0-DDLN-SWH-003 ID allocation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The RMT SHALL enforce that requirement numbers are allocated densely without
 repetition.
 Deleted requirements are replaced by placeholders.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Rationale: It is easier to track no requirements have fallen through the
 cracks if the tools to manipulate them can check they are all enumerated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verification: Unit test.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Parent:REQ-0-DDLN-SYS-005
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Safety Impact: None.
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
/req
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

